# Project Rules & Context Alignment

## Mandatory Initialization
* Before starting any task, read CLAUDE.md and README.md to understand the current tech stack, design principles, and project progress.

## Design & Aesthetic Standards
* Maintain a minimalist, high-end UI/UX.
* Follow the "White Space" and clear visual hierarchy rules.
* Use Tailwind CSS for all styling.
* Always use custom internal Modal components for confirmations (e.g., deletions). NEVER use native browser alert() or confirm().

## Logical Consistency
* Ensure data state is synced across all views (e.g., All Tasks and Project views must show the same status for shared tasks).
* Task deletion must be global across the entire application.

## Development Workflow
* Always work in a separate feature branch for new tasks (feat/...).
* Update CLAUDE.md and README.md after completing a major feature or logic change.